    <briefdescription>
<para>Simple day counter for reproducing theoretical calculations. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This day counter tries to ensure that whole-month distances are returned as a simple fraction, i.e., 1 year = 1.0, 6 months = 0.5, 3 months = 0.25 and so forth.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="warning"><para>this day counter should be used together with <ref refid="class_quant_lib_1_1_null_calendar" kindref="compound">NullCalendar</ref>, which ensures that dates at whole-month distances share the same day of month. It is <bold>not</bold> guaranteed to work with any other calendar.</para>
</simplesect>
<xrefsect id="test_1_test000180"><xreftitle>Test</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para>the correctness of the results is checked against known good values. </para>
</xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>
    </detaileddescription>
